p purples, greens, browns and tans. The beads were sewn tightly to the leather to keep them from causing noise. On her face she wore her amazonian mask.  <br>
<br>
Around her exposed thigh she had a dagger within it's sheath strapped to it and around her calf she had a dagger/sword within it's sheath as well. She wore what looked like heavy-sewn leather moccasins so that any steps she made in the future were silent. <br>
<br>
Strapped down the outer side of her covered thigh was what looked like little throwing darts, each was covered in a poison concoction of curare which acted as a muscle relaxant, causing eventual collapse of the muscles, crushing the heart and lungs and stopping them from working with a final result of death.  Strapped to her back was a sword given to her by a prince in India for her assistance in the elimation of a demon who fed on and raped the daughters of an indian village. And on her fingers, she wore a ten-set of rings. Each ring had a small, sharp blade that could easily cause damage to reptillian skin. She could add poison to the tips of these if she wanted too. And under the rings she wore black, rough leather gloves that gave her the advantage of a good grip.<br>
<br>
She was fully assorted and she had her powers as well, but her first resource would be her weapons at hand, not in hand.<br>
She walked with a strengthful stride to the edge of the village and suddenly shot up her hand in the air, and even through the glove she wore, a red light shot out of her palm and up into the sky.<br>
<br>
A sudden rumble in the distance caused the ground to shake for a moment before what was approaching bounded high above a large stretch of trees and landed paces away from her, giving one strong tremble to the ground.<br>
<br>
She closed her palm and looked upon one really LARGE tiger. It was white with black spots, easily visible through any forest, but this one could also camouflage. She gave the tiger a smile and it knelt down to let her on. It was the fair size of a good, strong horse and as he got on it, it purred a very rumbling purr. She treated it pretty much like a horse too, a horse that could eat meat and had fangs and claws.  She clicked her tongue and the tiger set out at a galloping-typed pace towards Delilah's willed destination to assist Alysia.<br>
<br>
